# Generated audit reports (regenerated by npm run ci / GH Actions on every
# run, embed a volatile timestamp, no gating role — centrality-baseline.json
# etc. own the actual thresholds). Tracking these made the tree perpetually
# dirty after every push since the pre-push hook regenerates them.
scripts/handler-regression/centrality-report.md
scripts/handler-regression/cohesion-report.md
scripts/handler-regression/coverage-report.md

# Claude Code session lock — transient per-session {sessionId,pid,procStart,
# acquiredAt} state, rewritten by every session that touches scheduling.
# Same perpetual-dirty-tree class as the audit reports above.
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
